reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 15, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Easy to see and use
reviews.reviewText: I got sick of these disappearing in my house! These are easy to see, sturdy and long enough for my old house's infrequent plugs. Would buy again.

reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars These are amazing charging cables!!
reviews.reviewText: They are nice and long and work extremely well!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 13, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Finally, I Know Which Charger Is Mine!
reviews.reviewText: Do you live with another person, and/or persons? If you do, then I'm sure you have had a conversation (perhaps heated) about whose charger is being used. My household was no different, everyone was asking "where is my charger?!", "Is that MY charger you are using?!"or "I left my charger right here and now it's gone!" so off to amazon I went to stop the madness!The good news, this product put order back into my home. These long braided lightning cables for our iPhones allowed us each to have our own color of charger. After that we could all easily identify our personal chargers from others in the household. It's great that they are also durable, and quickly charge my phone but for me the different colors were a game changer. Order has been restore to my household and I am grateful!

reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Long, rope cord
reviews.reviewText: I’ve bought these cords before but 6ft instead and I loved them! The only thing I will say is they can break down around where the charger plus’s into the phone and the cord meet if you’re not cautious. I can’t remember when I purchased but it’s been a few years at least.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 29, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Part of pin breaks off inside charging port
reviews.reviewText: These are the perfect length, they charge fast, they last a little while even with my teenagers, BUT this is the second one from which a piece broke off of the charging end and got stuck inside a device. Thankfully, after hours of searching the internet, I found someone who successfully removed it from their device with a safety pin and this has worked twice for me.
